data.title: Old Time Dairy Queen
data.text: This Dairy Queen is a walk-up with no inside seating or car service. It serves up great DQ fare in this nostalgic building. You'll see lots of classic cars here, remembering the days everyone "cruised the gut" and met in the DQ parking lot!

data.title: The First Dairy Queen ever built in Vancouver, WA as a drive-up place to eat!
data.text: My favorite foods are heath blizzards, chocolate sundaes, onion rings, and chicken sandwiches. Yes, it was recently remodeled in order to bring you quicker meals with excellent customer service. You will need to eat in your car because there is no restaurant seating here. It is approximately 50 years old. I've eaten here for years, and it is always good no matter what I order. The best fast food ice cream shop in town.

data.title: A Favorite For Our Family
data.text: This is the original DQ in Vancouver. They have recently remodeled which means quicker service. There is no inside dining here, but some tables and benches so it is a nice sunny day spot for lunch or after school treats. Or, you can eat in your car if you wish.

data.title: Above average for fast food burgers
data.text: This is a old style dairy queen with no seating.  You eat in your car.   I like it because the food is hotter than most fast food places.  if you order onion rings they fry them up fresh.  The hamburgers are not grilled(steam tray) but are made to order so they are hot and have not been sitting around.  They have dipped ice cream cones.
